# Zyntel Development Rules — Enterprise Best Practices

zyntel() => { "measured.managed"; }

## Stack (Kanta)
- Kanta: Next.js 14+ TypeScript, Supabase (Nairobi), Vercel. Phase 1: Vercel only (no Railway). Phase 2: api.zyntel.app on AWS Fargate.
- Database: Supabase PostgreSQL; plan_config for tier limits
- API: Versioned from day one — /api/v1/* never /api/*
- PWA: Workbox + IndexedDB offline scan queue

## Code Standards
- TypeScript strict mode always — no `any` types
- All API routes validate input with Zod before touching DB
- Env vars typed; never `process.env` directly
- Functional components; no class components

## Input Validation (Production-Grade)
- Validate at API boundary; never trust client input
- Use schemas with min/max, enums, regex where appropriate
- Reject malformed payloads with 400 and clear error (no 500 for validation)
- Sanitize strings before storage (trim, length limits)

## Error Handling
- Never swallow errors: log and rethrow or return structured error response
- Use custom error types; map to HTTP status codes consistently
- Never expose stack traces or internal paths to clients in production

## Logging
- Never log PII (names, emails, phones, patient data)
- Log levels: ERROR for failures, WARN for recoverable, INFO for key actions

## Security
- Security headers: CSP, HSTS, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options
- Rate limiting on auth and public endpoints
- No secrets in code or `.env` committed; use `.env.example` with placeholders only

## API-First
- Build endpoints before UI; backend serves UI, partners, future Zyntel API
- Version APIs: /api/v1/dashboard not /api/dashboard

## Git
- Branch: `feature/LINEAR-ID-short-description` or `feat/ENG-12-qr-code`
- Never commit directly to main
- PRs require review before merge
- Use `development` branch for staging deploys
